:"Deceased","1584":"1584","1550":"1550","3 February 1573":"3 February 1573","1639":"1639","about 1584":"about 1584","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Upcher","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Upsher  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Upsher","meanings":["English: habitational name from Upshire in Waltham Holy Cross (Essex), which derives from Old English <i>upp</i> ‘upper’ + <i>scīr</i> ‘district’. Compare   Abshire  ."]}]},{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Upcher married Richard Backler on 3 February 1573, in Dedham, Essex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1550–1584":"1550–1584","1584–1639":"1584–1639","–Female":"Surnud","1584":"1584","1550":"1550","3 February 1573":"3. veebruar 1573","1639":"1639","about 1584":"umbes 1584","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1550–1584":"1550–1584","1584–1639":"1584–1639","–Female":"Kuollut","1584":"1584","1550":"1550","3 February 1573":"3. helmikuuta 1573","1639":"1639","about 1584":"noin 1584","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1550–1584":"1550–1584","1584–1639":"1584–1639","–Female":"Décédée","1584":"1584","1550":"1550","3 February 1573":"3 février 1573","1639":"1639","about 1584":"environ 1584","Dedham, Colchester district, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Dedham, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Dedham, Essex, England":"Dedham, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joan Upcher a épousé Richard Backler le 3 février 1573, à Dedham, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1550–1584":"1550–1584","1584–1639":"1584–1639","–Female":"Verstorben","1584":"1584","1550":"1550","3 February 1573":"3. Februar 1573","1639":"1639","about 1584":"um 1